@{b}ECHO@{ub}

Usage: @{b}ECHO [expression]@{ub}

The ECHO instruction is a synonym for the @{"SAY" LINK "SAY/main"} instruction. It displays the
expression result on the console.

Example:
@{fg shine}
        echo  "You don't SAY!"
@{fg text}
